<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[96,709,891,1103]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
This is the mainland counterpart to the closely related 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waldock" authorityYear="2013" box="[190,336,921,946]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeruleus">
<emphasis box="[190,336,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M. caeruleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Mating by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otto &amp; Hill" authorityYear="2014" box="[490,601,921,946]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avibus">
<emphasis box="[490,601,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M. avibus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waldock" authorityYear="2013" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeruleus">
<emphasis box="[680,707,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[96,202,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">caeruleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can result in viable hybrids. In the laboratory one male hybrid mated with a female 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waldock" authorityYear="2013" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeruleus">
<emphasis box="[683,704,984,1009]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[96,202,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">caeruleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that laid eggs, resulting in several juvenile offspring. However two hybrid females that mated with hybrid males failed to produce any eggs.
</paragraph>
